yaru-theme (25.04.2-0ubuntu1) plucky; urgency=medium

  [ Marco Trevisan (Treviño) ]
  * gtk/common: Sync with window controls upstream changes (LP: #2107388)
  * tweaks: Adapt to window controls adjustments the upstream changes
    (LP: #2107388)
  * tweaks: Set proper size for window controls buttons (LP: #2106784)
  * gtk/tweaks: Use window controls padding and margins to be consistent with
    libadwaita (LP: #2106784)
  * gtk/meson: Fix parsing of accent and accent-optimized color codes
    (LP: #2107420)
  * gtk-2.0: Add wartybrown accented theme and assets (LP: #2107421)
    We didn't generate these assets, so some elements of the theme were not
    consistent with the actual accent, but more importantly when using the
    dark mode, the applications were close to unusable.
    Thus the huge diff, as we had to re-generate the theme assets for the
    accent.
    The assets and theme definitions are actually not new, so there's no UI
    change involved, they are just the same assets we ship for all the other
    accents, but rendered with the wartybrown color.

 -- Marco Trevisan (Treviño) <marco@ubuntu.com>  Wed, 16 Apr 2025 03:47:08 +0200

yaru-theme (25.04.1-0ubuntu1) plucky; urgency=medium

  [ Marco Trevisan (Treviño) ]
  * gnome-shell: Add missing keyboard-zwnj-symbolic icon
  * ci: Use minimal configuration for rendering icons
  * ci: Install base theme to make inkscape work
  * icons/render-bitmaps: Do not fail if directory exists already
  * ci: Enable GTK theme for rendering
  * ci: Install hub from sources instead of using a precompiled binary
  * ci: Run track-lp-issues job also on script changes
  * ci: Drop the in-house action to build deb files, reusing desktop team one
  * common: Generalize the yaru variants computation
  * gtk: Use meson native features to rename configured files
  * common/accent-colors: Use same contrast target as in libadwaita
  * cleanup: Remove warty nostalgia special theming
  * gnome-shell: Use upstream -st-accent-color
  * gnome-shell-colors: Reduce the delta with upstream default values
  * gnome-shell: Simplify colors code by just overriding what we need
